Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I go to Page 06 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Ovary, mass' from the dropdown menu
Then 'I describe' radio button is enabled and preselected
And 'I know' radio button is enabled
And 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is enabled and preselected
And 'Characterization II' tab is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis' tab is enabled

And 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

And 'Size' input field is enabled
And '2nd plane' input field is enabled
And '3rd plane' input field is enabled

And 'Circumscribed' radio button is enabled
And 'Non-circumscribed' radio button is enabled

And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

And 'Detection of a capsule' checkbox is enabled

And 'T1w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T2w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T1w signal FS' slide bar is enabled

And 'Focal signal voids' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Complex cystic' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Detection of a capsule' checkbox
Then 'Expansion beyond the capsule' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Complex cystic' checkbox
Then 'Nodular parts' checkbox is enabled
And 'Septa' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Septa' checkbox
Then 'Nodular parts' checkbox is enabled
And 'Focal thickening' checkbox is enabled
